inn1.comm: Almost cleaned up first ball. What a start. What a ball. It cut in sharply from outside off, from short of length and jagged in to hit the front pad and went over the stumps. There are a few cracks on the pitch; Jeff Dujon, on air, reckons it probably hit one of them.
Fine response from Masakadza. Full toss, a gift from Roach, and Masakadza creams it through covers.
around the off stump line, on a length, Masakadza leans forward to defend.
Fuller, looking for some movement, around the off stump, holds its line and Masakadza pushes inside the line and it runs off the outer edge to third man
another big in cutter ... cuts in with pace ... and the batsman gets an inside edge to the pad
outside off stump line, Sibanda pushes it out to point.
floated outside off stump, pushed away to the off side
slight turn, moving away from the off stump, defended on the back foot
gets well forward to push this flighted delivery to the off side
leans forward to drive to mid-off
outside off stump and just about holds its line, the batsman goes for the cut but the blade goes under the ball and he is beaten
straighter one on the off and middle line, pushed back down the track
leans forward to defend the length delivery to cover
Second boundary of the game. It was a short of length delivery outside off stump, Sibanda tried to fetch it from there with a pull shot but gets a lucky fat edge over the slips!
full in length, homing in on the off stump, Sibanda is late in getting forward for the drive and edges it to his pad
on that off stump line, skids on almost, again Sibanda seems a touch late in getting the bat down in time and squeezes it off the outer edge to second slip. It went all along the ground
bounces in from short of length, from outside off stump, Sibanda seems sure of his off stump and shoulders arms
fuller, on the middle and leg, Sibanda tries to flick, misses and is struck on the pad. Going down leg, though. There is not even an appeal.
outside off stump, mistimes the forcing shot off the back foot and the ball rolls to short cover
flighted slowly, fuller, the batsman gets forward to defend and edges it on to his pad
moves forward to work it wide of midwicket
beaten outside off . It lands on a length just outside off and turns away, the batsman pushes inside the line
leans forward to defend to short cover
gets on the back foot to punch it wide of backward point
full in length, around that off-stump line, Masakadza is caught at the crease, just leans forward to push it back down the track
stays back to work this to Barath at midwicket
Roach is cranking up some pace here. Unfortunately no speed gun on. This one is just outside off, defended on the front foot
on the middle stump line, short of length and he uses that length to clip it through midwicket, past Barath
shout for lbw and then for catch but NOT OUT! It cut in from just outside off, moved past the defensive prod and hit the pad high. It then bounded off to second slip but no wood on leather
gets behind the line of this one and pushes it out to the leg side
short in length and outside off, Sibanda rocks back to cut it well to the left of backward point
turns away from the off stump, Sibanda shapes to cut but is beaten
almost a yorker around off, dug out to the off side
fuller, leans forward to tap it to the on side
gets forward to work this past square-leg
length delivery on the middle and off line, Sibanda is again a touch late in getting forward and just about manages to keep it out
And again. The ball hit the bat there. Sibanda is being troubled by the pace.
length delivery on the middle stump line, Sibanda gets forward and this time plays a compact-looking defensive stroke
fuller and outside off, driven to the left of mid-off where Chanderpaul makes the stop
bounces in from back of length, around that off stump again, Masakadza gets forward to block it
fuller, around that off stump, straightening, pushed out to cover
floated on the off stump line. pushed back to the bowler
on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
fuller, very full but Sibanda pushes it softly towards mid-off
leans forward to push to cover
drops this one short and Sibanda goes back to cut but unlike in the previous over, he doesn't find the gap. Hit straight to backward point
gets forward to turn this flighted delivery straight to midwicket. This is the second maiden over for Benn
in the zone outside off stump, short in length, the batsman goes for the cut but doesn't connect
Neat shot. It was slightly short in length outside off stump, Masakadza stands up tall to punch it through covers. Pollard makes a nice sliding stop near the boundary
taps this one wide of point for a single
on the middle stump line, keeps a touch low, Masakadza just about manages to get the bat around his front pad to make some contact

run out chance missed short in length, turned to left of midwicket where Barath makes a fine sliding stop. Masakadza is in the middle of the pitch before he makes the journey back. Barath fumbles with the ball at this point as he shapes to throw and the split second delay allows the batsman to get back in time
Imperious response. He takes a couple of steps down the track and blasts the full pitched delivery wide of mid-off
leans forward to defend
outside off stump, Sibanda tries to play a cute little late dab and is beaten
drifts in to the middle and off line, pushed out to the off side
charges out to drive and hits hard but finds cover
slower in pace, tossed up fuller, driven straight to mid-off
on the pads, turned to square-leg. Another maiden over from Benn!
short and wide outside off, guided straight to third-man for a single
fuller on offstump, Sibanda drives to long-off and they take a single
same line, but totally different response! Whacks it from outside off over midwicket for a boundary, so nearly a six
full and straight, driven back to the bowler
lenght ball outside offstump, and the batsman mistimes it to cover,
homes in off offstump again. Gets forward to defend, but edges it onto his pads
blocked towards the offside
Benn's been very consistent with his line, no runs again
shorter this time, turned to backward point
full, nearly a yorker, batsman keeps it out
another maiden from Benn, bowls it again on offstump, defended for no runs.
a bit of intent from the batsman, tries to move outside leg, but cannot get it past Chanderpaul at mid-off, he fumbles and throws wide. An overthrow is taken.
fuller and homing in towards the pads, Sibanda keeps it out
full face of the bat, and driven back to the bowler for no runs
very good yorker, tailing in once again. Hits Sibanda's boot first, probably missing leg.
Another excellent ball from Smith, getting some movement. Beats the batsman all ends up and somehow misses the stumps.
straying towards legstump, driven firmly towards long on for a single to finish the over
a sure drop in pace from Roach to Smith to Pollard. Gentle loosener outside off, blocked away
shorter outside off, Sibanda throws his bat at it and cannot connect
fuller and the batsman nudges it with soft hands to pinch a single.
bowled from wider of the crease, angles it in this time short of a length. Defended off the backfoot.
width on offer, and the batsman uses it to steer it down to third man. No pace or movement for Pollard.
tight single again, hit between point and covers. Would have been close if the throw had hit, but all's well.
shorter and on middle and leg, turned away to midwicket for a run
Miller is on legstump again, fuller this time, played away for no runs
pulls out the sweep, along the carpet to square leg for a run
short and played off the backfoot for no run
fuller this time and elicits the drive, but straight to the fielder.
comes down the track, but there is a little spin for Miller this time. Sibanda negotiates it towards cover for a single.
takes a couple of steps down the track and tries to force it away, edges behind square-leg
leans forward to defend the length delivery
Smack! He charges down the track, the bowler shortens the length and Masakadza adjusts, lifts his back leg in the air as he shifts all his weight on the front foot and flat-bats it through covers
sprays this one to the pads and Masakadza clips it away very wristily to the boundary. Easy pickings.
slower one, full outside off, dabbed down to third man
leans forward to defend the length delivery
length delivery on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
leans forward to punch it to long-on
turns away from the stumps, Sibanda is beaten, pushing inside the line
leans forward to defend to the off side
moves down the track but is nearly beaten by the dip that Miller got, adjusts by lunging forward to defend
gets forward to ping long-off

short delivery, goes for the pull and the ball goes past the gloves and down the leg side. The bowler appeals and Simon Taufel responds by signaling a wide! The replays seemed to indicate that it hit the glove
short in length, around off and middle, pushed out to the on side
short of length, mistimes the intended cut to the off side
slips to the pads, turned past square-leg for a single
leans forward to push the slightly slower one back to the bowler
well outside off stump, almost a wide actually but the batsman chases it to run it down to the on side
gets forward to push it away for a single
leans forward to turn it to the on side for a single
shapes to sweep but doesn't connect properly
, just makes some room by moving to the leg side and punches it on the up and through the line and through covers

Given out lbw but it perhaps was missing the off stump. It was flighted on the off and middle line, Masakadza went for his sweep shot but missed. The ball hit the back pad around the line of off stump and it appeared as if it was turning away from the stumps. The umpire must have given it out as it struck the back-foot
slip in place and he watches Taibu get forward to defend
lovely delivery It drifts in, landed on a length almost on the middle stump line, Taibu got forward to defend but the ball spun past the bat
cuts in from just outside off, Sibanda is cramped for room as he shapes to punch on the up and pushes his bat outside the line of the ball which just about misses the off stump
well outside off stump, Sibanda tries to reach out with a cut but doesn't reach
stands up tall to punch it to through the off side for a single
short and wide, cut away but Smith intercepts with a dive at backward point
tapped to left of backward point and they rush across for a quick single
leans forward to defend a slow off cutter to cover
leans forward to defend to cover
Taibu is at it again. He goes for the reverse sweep now and misses it completely. He was out trying to repeatedly playing the conventional sweep shot in the t20 game
leans forward to defend to the o nside
turns away from the off stump, steered to point
slows up the pace, on the middle and off line, defended on the front foot
goes on the back foot to punch it to cover
chase and a miss. Well outside off stump, Sibanda lunges across to drive but meets thin air
stays back to chop this back-of-length delivery to third man
length delivery outside off, Taibu walks down the track and pushed it back to the bowler
perhaps because of the walk by Taibu in the previous delivery, Pollard pushes this one down the leg side
keeps a touch low, and outside off, taibu tries to chop it away but can't connect.
short in length, cut away to point
gentle seam-up delivery around off stump, guided to backward point
fuller, outside off, driven down to long-off
leans forward to drive the off break back to the bowler
goes well back to cut the short delivery from the off-stump line to deep point .. Barath rushes back to make a diving stop near the boundary
turns in to the middle and leg line, dabbed behind square-leg
turns from outside off stump, Sibanda goes really back to defend to the on side
leans forward to turn it to short midwicket
moves down the track and defends.
goes for the reverse sweep but is too early through with his shot and jabs it to slip
backs away to punch it to sweeper cover
quicker, on the middle and leg, worked to short midwicket
on the off and middle stump line, skids on from back of length, Sibanda pulls it down to long-on
slower, TAibu waits on a bent knee to sweep it to deep midwicket
outside off stump, guided past backward point, towards third man for couple of runs
full and on the legs, goes back to work it to mdiwicket
presses well back to jab it to the on side
moves down the track to drive to long-off
floated outside off, Taibu goes for the reverse paddle this time and edges it over Ramdin!
He goes for the reverse sweep again but doesn't connect ..
really full delivery, pushed to the bowler
short outside off, batsman dances down but blocks it towards cover
shorter, nudged off the backfoot for no runs
fuller this ime, but can't get a run on the leg side
nudged to off, misfield gives them two
swept to deep square leg for a run
lots of spin and Taibu very nearly guides it straight to Gayle at slip, but he takes it on the bounce.
full on offstump, blocked for no runs
comes down this time and drives to long on for a run
and again, Taibu steps out and drives along the ground stright for s single
shortens the length slightly outside off, defended to leg for no run
nudged away for a single through the legside
and again, Taibu picks it away through midwicket. They are milking the singles easily off the spinners.
Taibu fetches that from well outside off towards midwicket to get a rare boundary
and again, shuffles towards the offside and launches into that one in the air, one bounce four between midwicket and long on
Three in a row! Taibu finally connects a reverse sweep, and sweetly. Along the ground, behind point for four more
but that does not stop Taibu from trying another reverse sweep, paddles it to third man and they hares through for three.
really bad bounce, that stayed dangerously low, adds to Sibanda's woes but he keeps it out.
Taibu is in the groove. Sweeps very fine for a couple, that's easily the best over of the innings.
starts on midstump and spins well down leg, and its nudged for a tight single
stifled appeal as it raps Sibanda's pads, but it was turning down
made room and cut away in front of point for two
tight single through point

fulltoss above waist and the batsman is caught at deep square leg, but it is a no ball for height. The fielder had no idea, and ambled along as the batsmen scurried through for three. Poor cricket from the hosts
leans forward to ping long on for a run
half-stop by Gayle at short cover, and Pollard could have effected a run out at the bowler's end, but he missed. Overthrow again.
Worked towards midwicket for a run. Taibu has infused much-needed urgency
Sibanda beaten wide outside off, no run
closer to the stumps, but Sibanda is beaten again, neither forward nor back
gets bat on ball this time, guided to third man for a single
very full, yorker that beats the batsman, but its not on the stumps and goes through to Ramdin for no run
Sibanda reverse sweeps now! Picks two towards third man
shovels it towards the legside, but can only get a single
nudged away nicely by Taibu for a single through midwicket
another attempted reverse-sweep, mis timed to short cover
pulls back the length this time, and drags Sibanda down the track, but negotiated safely to the offside
full and straying on leg stump, Taibu clips it away to square leg for one
short of a length on offstump and guided to third man by Sibanda for a run.
same shot, different person. Taibu guides it to third man and gives Sibanda a chance to reach fifty. He's on 49
and he very nearly falls for 49. Beaten outside off yet again by Roach, but somehow escapes edging it.
shortens the length and Sibanda looks to pinch a single on the offside, but it goes straight to point
full this time and Sibanda punches it confidently off the front foot, but dead straight to short cover. No run
paddles it from wide outside off towards squareleg for a run.
and that's his fifty finally. Hops down the track and drives to long on, and comes back for a second.
tries another reverse sweep and does not connect
down the track again and punched straight down for one
very short and pulled away by Taibu. Shoddy fielding from Roach and Taibu comes back for two.
top-edges a sweep, but it falls in no man's land behind square.
he guides this one to third man. It's short of a length outside off and there's an easy single there for Taibu.
Pollard loses control of an attempted slower one and it slips towards leg side. Guided away
short ball, elicits the pull shot and its fielded well by Chanderpaul at square leg.
this time, very wide outside off. Its his fourth wide and at his pace, inexcusable
nice slower ball, the batsman cannot connect the hoick to midwicket.
driven to the offside for a single
wide outside off and Taibu is hellbent on sweeping it all the way across, doesn't succeed
this time Taibu decides to play it to the offside, lovely deft touch towards third man for four
and its back to muscles towards the legside! Strongly swept behind square for four and that's a wonderful 50.
the attempted sweep goes very fine this time, off the glove, and Taibu comes back for two more
full outside off, exquisitely driven to sweeper cover for a single
comes down the track and takes it on the full, drives it down to long on for a single.
length delivery around off and middle, pushed out to short cover
Clubbed! He walked towards off stump, waited on the front foot, fetched it from outside off and swung it to midwicket boundary. Thwack!
banged in short around off, pulled down to left of short midwicket where Barath makes a fine stop
again moves towards off stump and swings the full delivery from outside off to long-on
banged in short outside off, Taibu waits before opening the bat-face and upper cutting it down to third man
slower one, full and on the off stump and Sibanda goes for the reverse sweep! doesn't quite connect well and the ball rolls away
floated outside off, driven to short cover
goes back to punch it back to the bowler
outside off, short in length, goes for the cut but is beaten by the lack of bounce there
gets forward to drive and drives well but straight to short cover
moves outside off, exposing all three sticks, and sweeps it to long leg
drops it short and Sibanda plays a crunching pull to wide long-on region where Smith makes a fine stop on the run

trapped in front. Taibu's fine innings, full of improvisations, has ended. It landed on a length just outside off and moved in with the angle. Taibu was on the front foot, looking to just tap it to the on side but some how missed to make contact and was hit on the back pad. Bit of a tame dismissal. Fine innings, though.
short and climbing outside off, Taylor tries to upper cut it to third man but no wood on leather
another short lifting delivery, slow pace, Taylor connects with his upper cut to third man this time
fuller, on the middle and off line, pushed back to the bowler

Super cool left footer from Pollard and Taylor is run out . full delivery just outside off, Sibanda stays back for some reason and just about manages to jab it to the off side, not all that far away from the stumps. Pollard rushes forward to kick it with his left foot and finds the stumps!
bouncer on the middle and leg stump line, the batsman allows it to pass over his left shoulder
lands on a length around off stump and Sibanda gets forward to push it to the off-side of the pitch
on the middle and leg line, swept away behind square-leg. They think about the second run but Sibanda slipped at the non-striker's end .. but both batsmen get back inside the crease safely in time
one slip in place ... on the middle and leg, attempted sweep but doesn't connect
turns from the off stump, stops a bit on the batsman, checks his push and it runs off the edge to point
leans forward to guide this one to point
stays back to punch this one from the off and middle line to sweeper cover and they run really hard to get back for the second run
really full delivery outside off stump line, Sibanda waits on the back foot to play a lovely late-cut through to third man
again pretty full, pushed out to the on side
leans well forward to drive to short cover
turns from the off stump line, shapes to defend but holds his bat inside the line
leans forward to ping long-off
floated full on the off stump line, driven to short cover
on the middle and off line, pushed out to cover for a single
on the middle and leg line, swept for a single
sharp turn there .. from the off stump line, beaten comprehensively
stays back to punch it to sweeper cover for a single
drifts in on the off stump line and spins away sharply, past the defensive prod
steers through to deep cover
around the off stump, turning away, guided to backward point for a single .. the throw comes in and goes down to long-on.. one more run
leans forward to drive to long-off
slows up the pace, short in length, cut away through cover point
gets forward to work this one through the on side
leans forward to tap it to point
Top shot. He stayed in the back foot, waited for the short delivery to arrive before punching it through extra cover
on the middle, much fuller this time, driven down to long-on
floated on the middle and leg line, tries to whip it to the on side but doesn't conenct
gets down the track and drives to long-off
lands around off and turns away, the batsman goes for the big swing to the on side and misses
wide down the leg side ..  goes past the attempted sweep
leans forward to push it to cover
backs away to the leg side and cuts from the off stump line but can't beat the off-side field
Flat six! Feisty hit. floated on the middle stump line, fierce slog sweep on a bent knee and it sails over midwicket
almost yorker length around off, squeezed out to short third man
moves back to force it to left of cover where Bernard, the sub, fails to stop it cleanly
leans forward to push it to cover
fires in a high full toss, pushed away past point
dropped short ball and elicits the pull. Two fielders - Pollard and Miller converge on it, and they fluff it.
drifting on leg and worked away off the backfoot through the leg side for a run.
anad short on leg and again pulled, but this time its more controlled. Single
on offstump this time, and the batsman defends to the offside. Looks for a single, but no chance
short again, angling in and misses everything - the pull shot and the stumps. No runs
short and wide outside off, Sibanda looks to thwack it through the offside and makes no contact
Full and tailing into leg, scooped over the head of point and it nearly runs away to the boundary before Barath pulls it back in
shorter and just outside offstump, dragged towards long on for one
slower ball, and it rolls through after pitching. No run
hit high towards long on, Chigumbara could not get enough bat on that and hence did not get enough distance. Good innings and a crucial breakthrough
shorter and outside off, tries to hit it hard through the offside and cannot connect
and at long last, Sibanda gets bat on one of those outside off. A good time to do so too, the field is in for the last ball of Power-play and it runs away for four behind square
very full on offstump, the batsman looks to come forward, but is not able to work it away. No run
low fulltoss outside offstump, he manages to scoop it towards third man for a single
another yorker, and Sibanda can't get it past cover
Slower delivery, and Sibanda misses a heave. It misses the stumps too.

a variation gone awry! The ball goes straight out of the bowler's hand, straight towards the batsman's face. He falls, recoups, drops his bat, recoups and completes a single. Its been that kind of day for Sibanda.
thickish outside edge flies very fine. Fletcher makes an impossible effort to stop it, but that was always four.
taps the short of length ball to the leg side and sets off for a run
slow slower ball outside off, the batsman waits and taps it towards third man for a run
ducks in from short of a length towards legstump. The batsman scamper a run as Pollard tries another kick on to the stumps. Misses this time.
taps to cover and runs through for another single. Zim need fours here
another almighty heave meets thin air. Shortens the length and misses the bat and stumps. No run
Sibanda hits one so sweetly! Picked the line early, got into that one and lofted it high and handsome behind square for a big six.
and again! He sure prefers it on the leg stump. Bad line from Pollard and Sibanda hits it squarer this time for four to the left of square leg.
full and slightly wide of off, Matsikenyeri can't get it away, no run
slower ball, gets big on the batsman and picks the edge, but it does not have enough to carry to Ramdin.

Smoking guns! Roach literally and otherwise breaks through the defences of the batsman. The bat is broken in two, the off bail has fallen off and Sibanda has to go. A bizarre end to an innings that was for most part, bizarre.
full toss on leg, guided away for one.
guides it towards cover for a single.
full on offstump, tries to punch it through cover, but can't pierce the infield, no runs
full and wide outside off, tries to sweep Benn, but can't get bat on ball
slashed away to third man for four! Very short and wide enough for the batsman to throw his bat at that one. It ran really fine.
very full, and goes in the same direction, but straight to short third man.
swept the fulltoss smartly from outside off, only one
Zimbabwe go past 250 with four byes! Ramdin can't stop it as it goes through his legs all the way.
can't connect the slog sweep and it runs away for another single

inn2.comm: round the wicket, homing in on middle, Gayle comes forward and blocks
shorter and slicits an airy drive, eludes short mid off
shorter still, grips and spins away from Gayle. Keeps low. Hmm.
and low bounce once again, outside off. Gayle plays it away to the legside.
draws him forward this time. Gayle taps it down the ground.
strays on leg, taps it to the on side and takes off, but Barath sends him back. Almost a run out, but the throw was wide. Maiden to begin with.
short of length on off and middle, turned away to midwicket for no run
fuller, draws Barath forward to smother the spin.
and again, on offstump and blocked away to the legside.
strays to leg this time, but Barath can't get it away
Big appeal. Not given, arm ball coming in raps him in front ofmiddle, but he was well forward and it was missing leg.
and we have two maidens to start proceedings. Barath safely negotiates a ball on offstump off the front foot.
Gayle taps to the legside and takes a single. West Indies are away.
short of a length, spinning in to Barath. He defends off the front foot.
similar length on offstump, punched back to the bowler
and again. Barath is not able to play it square for a single.
pulls out the sweep shot to one that drifted on to legstump and made good contact. West Indies have their first boundary.
turns it in from Gayle's offstump towards leg. He clips it to long on for single, was in the air a bit, but no one close in to take it.
shorter on legstump, raps the pads, but is going well down
comes into the right hander, safely played to the legside
taps it to cover and looks to steal a run, but its gone straight to the fielder. Tight stuff from Zimbabwe.
short, really short and Gayle takes full toll. Whacks it high over midwicket for six.
short again, but Gayle cannot make contact as he tries to get it through the offside.
fuller, Gayle comes forward and taps it in front of point for one.
this one holds its line and Barath defends it down towards the offside. No run
shorter, Gayle guides it off the backfoot to long on
Barath looks to make room, but cannot get it to the offside, pats it back to the bowler
attempts a sweep, and gets a leg bye towards short fine leg
draws Gayle forward and he taps it back
more leg-stump-ish line this time, Gayle looks to chip it down to long on, but does not succeed
succeeds this time, single down to long on

see you later! Gayle dances down the track with the kind of authority you come to expect of him. A flick of the wrists sends it high and handsome, it makes a hole on a window outside the ground. Clean hit, clean as they come.
super response from the bowler. Shortens the length ever so slightly and gets turn, beats the outside edge.
cat and mouse game on here. Gayle comes down again, but does not get the length to hit.
stays back and punches this one beautifully through the offside.
shift the line towards legstump, Gayle looks to sweep, but can't beat short fine
jumps out and smashes it hard down the ground, all the way for a single. Straight to long on.
short of a length, Gayle plays it away carefully
knocked down to long on for a single
and he's down the track again, tries to work it to the legside, but can't find the gap
Barath plays it to the leg side for no run
tight line on offstump, Barath looks to guide it past point and does not succeed

and the pressure is off. Similar ball, similar shot and they go for a tight single this time, there is a shy at the striker's end and the ball misses the stumps, but Gayle would have made his ground. And what's more - it's four overthrows.
short and turns into  Barath. He defends
Barath needs to turn the strike, but he can't. Tight lines from Utseya.
drives down the pitch, Utseya dives across and saves a run.
he finally gets it away to long on. No timing from Barath
pitches on Gayle's legstump and he turns it towards the midwicket area and takes a single
short of a lenght from Price, Gayle stays back and taps it towards midwicket
another tight single. Barath turns the ball towards the legside off his back foot. A direct hit would have made things interesting.
Gayle chips down and takes another single towards long on
On Barath's legstump, full, but he can't get any timing going. No run
and again. Shorter this time, but he can't pierce the legside circle.
Price continues to bowl on a tight leash. Pitches on off from his natural left-armers angle and straightens. barath taps it off the backfoot. No intent to score off that ball.
very low bounce again. short of a length on offstump, but does not sit up at all
a little leading edge there, but thankfully for Gayle it falls safely at mid on. Single
Barath continues to block. Full outside off, draws him forward and he defends.
straighter and Barath works it to the legside, straight to the fielder
same ball, same result, Barath needs to break free

and break free, he does! Lovely sweep shot to a ball that was drifting down leg. He found the gap at long leg to perfection. That's the second time he's swept to the boundary. Significant, given he's scored 15 off 36 balls.
middle and leg line, Gayle turns it off the front foot for no runs.
down the track, but can't get it past Price who effects a smart save, and he's really pumped up.
again, goes past Price's half-stop, but he tidies up. No run
gets it past this time, down to long off for one
drifts onto Barath's pads and he nudges it square on the legside
down the track, but refrains from going over the top. He wasn't to the pitch of it and chose to play it along the ground to long on
leans forward to defend to the off side
goes down the track, the ball drifts in, dips, lands and takes the outside edge of the intended flick and runs to short third man
moves forward to on drive to long-on
spins in from outside off, shuffles across to turn it past square-leg
around off stump, pushed on the front foot
drifts in from round the stumps, punched down to long-off
on the middle and leg, worked to backward square-leg
on the front foot and on driven to long-on
on the middle stump line, defended to the on side
on the middle, eased to long-on for a single
on the middle and leg, loopy flighted delivery, Gayle flicks uppishly and Cremer dives to his left at midwicket but doesn't reach it. cry of agony from Price
on the front foot, worked to short midwicket
moves down the track and takes it on the pad
on the middle, pushed back to the bowler
presses back to push the ball on the middle stump line back down the pitch
slows up the pace, Gayle gets on the front foot to drive to long-off
leans forward to work it past square-leg ..
on the middle and leg, from round the stumps, goes for the sweep and doesn't connect well
on the middle and leg, jabbed to short fine-leg
on the leg and middle, turns, defended on the front foot
turns from just outside leg, tapped to the on side
drops it short and Barath quickly presses back, waits before he cuts it well to the left of backward point
on the middle and off, steered to cover point
taps this leg break towards square-leg for a easy single
short and wide, Gayle mistimes the cut shot to right of cover but will pick up the single
short in length, decent pace (no speed gun, so not sure!), cuts in with bounce to hit the thigh pad
sprays to the legs and Barath tickles it to fine-leg boundary. Flicked away
again lands it outside leg stump, turned to long-.leg. Free hit coming up folks and Gayle on strike!
Whack! What a deliciously violent hit. It was short and just outside off, Gayle cleared the front foot and whacked it over wide long-on boundary. Crash!
outside off stump, fuller in length, steered past point
back of length outside off stump, guided to backward point
leans forward to drive to long-off
moves well forward to off drive to long-off

Gayle presses forward to clip it past square-leg and he rushes hard to come back for the second run .. wild throw at the non-striker's end .. ah ..it hit something near the square-leg region where it bounced and turned direction
on the front foot and drives to long-on
superb delivery. It drifted in, landed around middle stump lne, gripped and turned past the tentative defensive prod
works this one through the on side for a single
punches this one to the off side
spins in sharply from outside off, Barath is cramped as he shapes to cut and just about stabs the ball away
leans forward to mistime a off drive back to the bowler
slower, outside off, Barath chases the wide delivery, tries to cut but doesn't connect
outside off stump, taps behind the wicket and Taibu stretches to his right to stop it
pushes this one to point
again shapes to cut but yet again is cramped for room by the spin; jabs it away in the end
turns down the leg side ... wide
Ah! the reverse sweep from Gayle, 50 up! It was around the off stump line, Gayle suddenly chose to play the reverse sweep and gets it third-man boundary.
leans forward to drive it back down the track
on the middle and leg,worked to midwicket
quicker one, skids on outside off, Barath is once again beaten on the cut shot
from round the stumps, drifts down the leg side, full, Gayle goes for the sweep and Taibu collects really well
on the leg stump line, worked past square-leg
turns in from outside off and I can't believe that Barath has not still figured out the cut shot is going to be risky when it turning .. again cramped for room and jabs it out in the end
full and outside off, left alone this time
taps this one to short midwicket
turns in from outside off, steered to backward point
quicker one but goes down the leg side  and taibu deflects it to short fine-leg
low dipping full toss, driven to long-off
moves down the track and whips the full delivery to deep square-leg region
turns in to the middle stump line, tapped behind square-leg
drives on the front foot, the bowler dives to his left to make a half-stop
turns to the middle and off line, tapped to the on side
on the middle and leg, spins in towards middle. Barath squeezes it out unconvincingly to the off side
eases this one to long-on
leans forward to wrist the flighted delivery to short midwicket
tossed up outside off, driven to sweeper cover
from round the stumps, on the middle stump, swept down for a single

goes back to turn it to short fine-leg region  .. Barath sets off for a single, is sent back and dives to get back inside the crease. It was refered upstairs and he is home. Had it been a direct hit, he would have been a goner
moves down the track and drives down to long-on

Trapped in front! Huge wicket this. It drifted in from round the stumps, lands on the middle stump line, and straightens to hit him in front of middle. That's out. Gayle had pressed his front leg across, perhaps tad too across, and had to play around the front pad. Too late. Gone! What a strike by Lamby!
gets forward to on drive to long-on
on the middle stump line, turned to short midwicket
quickish, turns from outside off, Chanders is hit on the front pad, trying to defend but is struck outside off
shapes to cut , the ball spins in and he guides it to short third man
leans forward to defend to the on side
another shout for lbw but struck just outside off stump. Again Chanderpaul was looking to defend but pushed outside the line
moves down the track and drives towards non striker and the bowler makes a diving stop
leans forward to tap it to the on side
spins in from outside off, guided to short third man
spins in from outside off and there goes Barath for the cut shot . cramped up again and the ball rolls to the off side

Whoa! Barath breaks free with a big hit down the ground. He lunged forward and swung it high over the bowler's head. I thought he had sliced it too much and it would go right up in the air and not clear the distance but it kept sailing ...
turns in from outside off, tries to work it away to the legside, but does not succeed
gets forward to a fuller delivery and chips it to long on for a run
very short and extremely wide down the leg, misses Barath's attempt to pull
tries to nurdle it down to third man and is beaten
jumps out and tries to hit over long on, but does not connect well enough
short outside offstump and cut away to deep point
on a length outside off, Chanderpaul rocks back and plays it away towards cover for one
drifting on Barath's pads and he works it away behind square for a single
worked away off the back-foot to mid-on
comes down the track and manages to get an outside edge into the offside. Lamb's turning it a bit.
full on legstump and Barath is content to work the singles. To long leg this time.
on a length, turns from leg towards middle. Defended
turns big, but its very short. Cut away off the backfoot towards deep cover
goes straight on and drifts towards leg, hits Barath's pads
swept the full delivery towards deep square leg
turn again, but the line is too straight. Drifts onto Chanders' pads and he works it very fine
short outside off, easily cut away off the back foot towards cover
On middle and leg, tries to work it past short fine, but cannot.
taps a length-ball off the front foot towards the bowler
big bounce outside off, and Barath is surpised as he tries to work it down to third man
drifting down the leg again, Barath flicks away to deep backward square leg for a single
short of a length and some turn again, but very slow turn, Chanderpaul stays back and taps it behind point for a run.
short of a length on legstump, worked away off the back foot
super fielding at third man. Short and wide, and Barath frees his arms and cuts it well. The fielding restricts him to two, but thats enough for his 50.

And that's out! Bowling change works, pace change works. Short again, but not so wide and Barath again looks for an expansive cut, but only manages to get an inside edge. The stumps are rattled and Barath is gone.
short of a length on off stump. Blocked safely down the ground.
similar ball, Fletcher plays it safely on the on side
back of a length, and pushes the batsman to the back foot. No chance of a run.
full on offstump, driven down to long off for a single
on a length outside offstump, but it turns in. Fletcher plays it away to midwicket
fuller and Fletcher pats it back to Lamb
finally gets a single to get off the mark, but Zimbabwe won't mind it since Fletcher retains strike
slow looping fulltoss on offstump, driven down the ground for a single.
on a length, on his offstump and Chanderpaul works it away to cover for one
shorter outside offstump, and turning in. Fletcher drives it off the back foot to long on
legstump line, patted back by Chanderpaul
short and wide outside off, gives Chanderpaul room to guide it through the covers
hops down the track and chips the length ball to long on. A bit of a fumble, but they would have picked two anyway.
grip and turn, from middle to off. Chanderpaul plays it away safely
comes down the track but can't get to the pitch. Plays it in the air back to the bowler
keeps low, but is short enough to be safely negotiated to midwicket for one

Well well, what do we have here! Fletcher is gone. Short again and drifting down. He runs it down to short fine leg and turns back for two, but Cremer barreled in a superb throw. Taibu fails to collect, but that was a guided missile heading for the stumps all the same. Deflects off his gloves on to the stumps and Fletcher is well short. The third umpire spent a long time deciding, but it was clear from the first replay. Cremer's the man!
short of a length and turns away from offstump. Played away off the back foot.
leading edge to a full delivery on leg stump, but no danger there. Pops away harmlessly onto the offside.
back of a length outside off, tapped away off the backfoot.
on a length on middle stump, Chanderpaul is walking all around his crease, and works it down towards midwicket
really short, and gave the batsman enough time to rock back and pull it from wide outside off to the midwicket fence. Diving attempt on the boundary, but it is four.
Tapped off the front foot to point for a quick single.
today's a day for reverse-sweeps. Almost pre-meditated, gets good bat on that but not past short third-man.
cut away behind point for an easy run
full on leg stump, draws the batsman forward but he can't get it past the bowler
drifting down and worked away for a quick single
he is homing in on that full leg-stump line and Chanderpaul is not able to get it away.
outside off this time and Chanderpaul stays back and guides it through the covers
full and gets the outside edge as the batsman comes forward, but this is a really slow and low pitch. It trickles down to short third man for a single
short and outside off stump, forced off the back foot , down to long-off
short in length, slanting across Chanderpaul who cuts to left of backward point where Sibanda makes a diving half-stop
full pitched outside leg stump, flicked down to fine-leg region
full in length, outside off stump, guided to left of the diving Sibanda at backward point for a single
full and wide outside off stump
leans across to force this one to sweeper cover
full in length, outside off stump, chanderpaul tries to lean across and in the end just takes off the bottom hand off the handle and goes through with the uppish drive over extra cover
on the leg and middle, Chanderpaul tries to work it to the on side and gets a leading edge to cover
on the middle and leg, this time he turns it past square-leg
works this through the on side for couple of runs
outside off stump, turns away, punched to deep cover
on the leg and middle line, swept away for a single
spins away from the off stump, tapped towards short third man
turns in from the middle stump to hit the pad .. going down leg

dropped by Cremer. very difficult chance. Deonarine moved down the track and went for the big drive and it went off the inner half of the bat well to the left of cremer who stretched his left hand out but couldn't hold on
sweeps it to backward square-leg
goes for the big sweep and misses it completely .. he was off balance while playing it  .. the ball spins past the leg stump and past Taibu
skidder that keep a touch low, Chanders crouches to keep it out

Deonarine is run out  There was an lbw shout and then a run out. Drama. Action. It was the skidder that went on straight on the leg and middle line, Chanderpaul tries to turn it to the leg side and misses. Close shout for lbw turned down by the umpire. Deonarine tries to get across for a single. Mistake. Chanders is not interested and both end up in the striker's end. Taibu rushes to his left, dives to make the stop and throws it back at the non-striker's end. Gone!
floated full on the off stump line, nudged to the off side
straighter one, full on the middle and off line, Pollard pushes it back to the bowler
slows up the pace, around the off stump, pulled down to long-on
picks the ball from the off stump line and sweeps it to deep square-leg region
goes for the sweep again and picks up a single
moves forward to drive to long-on and retains the strike
gets forward to drive uppishly but safely through mid-off region, down to long-off fielder
on the middle stump line, turns to the on side
around the off stump line, full, Chanderpaul leans across to cream it through covers
skips down the track and drives to long-off
on the leg and middle line, drifts down leg, tickled to fine-leg region .. ah it goes off the pads ...

dropped by the bowler oh what a costly miss.. not an easy chance, though ...., cutting to middle and leg, Pollard tries to dab it to the on side and jabs it off the leading edge back down the track .. its in the air ... Chugumbura lunges low to his right but the ball dies on him and he just can't get his palms under the ball .. it looped across, not fast but just dipped on the bowler
picks up the leg bye this time and gets off strike
from round the stumps, length delivery outside off, pushed wide of cover
gets forward to stab a  delivery that climbs from short of length to the off side
length delivery around the off stump line, punched down to long-on
slower one from round the stumps, on the off stump line, pushed out to right of cover, wants a single but is sent back by Pollard
lovely slider on the off stump line, skids on straight... Pollard just about manages to stab it off the inner edge at the last minute
Chanders unfurls the reverse sweep .. he turned around and swept it high over short third man!

Oh boy he does it again. The bowler holds his head. The crowd cheer. Chanders punches Pollard's gloves. He again turned around, picked the ball around off stump line and swept it past that short third man
leans forward to flick it through midwicket
slider again, on the middle and leg. pollard is not picking it but again lunges out to stab it away
presses right back, plays it off the pitch and pushes it to the off side
starts off with a wide down the leg side
on the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
this time a wide outside off .. Pressure.
And could have been a wide down the leg side .. Chanderpaul goes for the sweep and edges it to his body
around the off stump, shoveled towards mid-off

Pollard falls. Zimbabwe captain breaks through. It was a loopy flighted delivery on the middle stump line, Pollard doesn't quite get forward, just on drives, sort of chips it uppishly, and straight to mid-on. Chanderpaul is still out there. West Indies five down. Pressure. Game on.
on the middle and leg, driven wide of mid-on for a single
moves down the track and taps a ball around leg stump to midwicket
around the off stump line, pushed to left of cover
quicker one, just outside off stump, punched to cover
gets back to work this to midwicket
moves outside leg stump line, cuts to cover
dot ball. More pressure. Flicked to midwicket
low full toss, dips on Ramdin who just manages to nudge it to short fine-leg
Chanders knows all is on him and he pulls off a boundary. He charged out, got outside the line and drove inside out to wide long-off boundary
nearly a yorker, pushed out back to the bowler ... good delivery
moves down the track, drives hard but can't beat mid-off. Just a single. Chanderpaul is not happy with himself. Ramdin on strike. Can he get it away?

run out missed Chanders escapes! What a miss from Utseya. He did well to move to his right to stop the ball but throws wide of the stumps at the non-striker's end ! chanderpaul was down the track and Utseya could have just run back and broken the stumps .. they then take the singel
leans forward to drive to the off side
full delivery, driven back to the bowler
goes for an expansive sweep, but just about clears the inner ring. Brings up another fifty for Chanders.
pulls out the reverse-dab to a fullish delivery. Fumble and a save keeps it down to one.
Ramdin tries to create room, Price follows him, and he can only drive down to long on for one
jumps out and misses a fulltoss. Hits it straight to short midwicket
stays back and drives down to long on for a single

Ramdin picks it up and goes high over mid on, but does not hit it hard enough. The batsmen scamper through for two and Chanders runs into Price. The batsman is down and Price gives him a hand. Good spirit.
length ball on leg stump, Chanders picks it up and hits towards long on.
change of pace, much slower and drops short outside off. Ramdin is early into the shot and manages to slap it towards midwicket
full and wide outside off, Chanders can't time it, hits it straight to short extra-cover
slow, but very accurate yorker. Ramdin tries to pick it onto the legside, but no luck.
again very full, low fulltoss. This time Ramdin gets bat on it, but only for a single. Zimbabwe don't mind this one bit.

Big moment! Huge moment! Chanderpaul knew that this ball had to go and would have tried to whack this anyway, but it helps that it is a big no-ball. Chanders shovels the length ball high and handsome straight down the ground for six. And here comes the free-hit.

short ball, pulled away to midwicket and he runs back for a really tight two. A more powerful throw would have nailed it, but this one bounced a couple of times from deep midwicket and Chanders had just enough time to dive in. Third umpire says not out, but only just.
Wide down the legside. The momentum is shifting, but West Indies need some more big ones.
short and wide outside off and cut away towards point for a single.
Chanderpaul, take a bow! He hops outside off and manufactures a shot out of nowhere. Shovels it over fine leg for another vital four. They are getting the thrust here.
goes over the offside this time. Short of a length on offstump, and Chanders goes down on a knee and whacks it to deep extra cover
hit very hard to short midwicket and the ball explodes through the fielder. Two runs. 22 from 14!

BIG wicket! Chanderpaul is gone and this game is far from over. Picks the length ball and times it beautifully, probably too beautifully, it carries to Chigumbura at long off, who is standing a few paces in, but holds his nerve and more importantly, holds the catch.
swing and a miss! Short of a length outside off, and misses the attempted pull
rubbish ball, loses the plot and fires it well wide of leg stump.
super comeback! Full yorker and more importantly follows the batsman as he tries to make room. Dot ball!
great line again, does not hit the yorker length but its good enough. Superb re-adjustment of radar after that wide.
full, tailing down leg and they pick a leg bye
He's a goner! Superb bowling here, keeps it straight and simple. Ramdin goes for an almighty heave through the covers and makes contact with thin air. Timber is struck and he'll have to go back.
another yorker, and Miller manages to squirt it to the offside for a run. Smith has strike. Will he look to keep it, or go for broke?
its the latter! Marginally fuller and down the leg and that's all the help Smith needs to free his hands. He deposits it behind square for a crucial boundary. Great shot under pressure.
Well, Miller has other plans! Picks up the length ball on leg stump and whacks it over midwicket for six. Stay at the other end, Smith! 9 required off 5!
slasher! wide outside off and he throws the kitchen-sink at it, flies towards the vacant third man fence. Miller's the man!
gets good hold of that one, but hits it straight to deep cover. Strike to Smith.

and he botches it up! Great ball under pressure from the debutant, but in the circumstances a really ordinary shot from Smith, who looks to hit the straight ball across the line. He misses and the stumps are rearranged. Benn walks out to the middle. 4 off 2!

Big Benn falls! Cremer holds on to a steepler and West Indies are succumbing to pressure! Benn goes for an almighty hoick over midwicket and hits it really high. Cremer runs in a long way from the deep midwicket fence and takes it millimetres off the ground. Super catch! 4 off 1, and the batsmen did not cross over, would you believe it!
another inch perfect yorker and he seals the deal in style! Take a bow Masakadza junior! Keeps it on legstump, very full and No. 11 Roach could not do more than squeeze a single to the leg side.
